{
  "info": {
    "name": "SOLO API",
    "description": "Import this file in Postman: **Import** ā†’ **Upload Files** ā†’ choose `backend/postman/SOLO-auth.postman_collection.json`.\n\n**Setup:** Set collection variables **`baseUrl`** (e.g. `http://localhost:4000` ā€” include `http://` or `https://`) and **`accessToken`** (Supabase JWT; `Bearer` is added per request). **`ideaId`** / **`objectiveId`** are set when **Create** requests return **`201`** (Tests tab), or paste UUIDs from list/create flows.\n\n**Swift controllers vs this collection**\n- **`IdeaController`** / **`IdeasRemoteDataSource`** ā†’ **Ideas** folder (**`GET/POST /ideas`**, **`PATCH`** / **`PUT /ideas/:id`**, **`DELETE /ideas/:id`**).\n- **`ObjectiveController`** / **`ObjectivesRemoteDataSource`** ā†’ **Objectives** folder (**`POST/PATCH/DELETE /objectivesā€¦`**, **`POST ā€¦/complete`**).\n- **`AuthController`** uses **Supabase Auth only** (no calls to **`{{baseUrl}}`**). Test **`login`**, **`signUp`**, **`googleSignIn`**, **`resetPassword`**, **`logout`** against your **`SUPABASE_URL`** GoTrue API or Supabase dashboard ā€” not this collection unless you add those requests yourself.\n- **`IdeaSearchController`** is an empty coordinator (no HTTP yet).\n\nIf **Update idea** fails with connection errors, check **`ideaId`** in the resolved URL (**Postman Console**) or try **PUT** instead of **PATCH**.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:4000"
    },
    {
      "key": "accessToken",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "ideaId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "objectiveId",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/health"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Ideas",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List ideas (fetchIdeas)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/ideas?sort=created_desc&q=",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["ideas"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "sort",
                  "value": "created_desc",
                  "description": "title_asc | created_desc | created_asc | updated_desc"
                },
                {
                  "key": "q",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "Optional search string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Maps to **`IdeaController.fetchIdeas`** ā€” lists ideas for the authenticated user (`[]` if empty)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create idea (createNewIdea)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data && data.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('ideaId', data.id);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"My idea title\",\n  \"purpose\": \"Why this exists\",\n  \"description\": \"Optional details\",\n  \"targetUser\": \"Optional audience\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/ideas",
            "description": "Maps to **`IdeaController.createNewIdea`**. **`title`** and **`purpose`** required. Response **`201`** ā€” Tests script stores **`id`** in **`ideaId`**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update idea (editIdea) PATCH",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Updated title\",\n  \"purpose\": \"Updated purpose\",\n  \"description\": \"Optional; omit keys you do not want to change\",\n  \"targetUser\": \"Optional\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/ideas/{{ideaId}}",
            "description": "Maps to **`IdeaController.editIdea`** ā€” same **`PATCH`** as **`IdeasRemoteDataSource.updateIdea`**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update idea (editIdea) PUT",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Updated title\",\n  \"purpose\": \"Updated purpose\",\n  \"description\": \"Optional; omit keys you do not want to change\",\n  \"targetUser\": \"Optional\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/ideas/{{ideaId}}",
            "description": "Same body/responses as **PATCH** if your proxy blocks **`PATCH`**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Toggle published (togglePublished) PATCH",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Same as stored title\",\n  \"purpose\": \"Same as stored purpose\",\n  \"description\": \"Optional\",\n  \"targetUser\": \"Optional\",\n  \"isPublished\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/ideas/{{ideaId}}",
            "description": "Maps to **`IdeaController.togglePublished`** ā€” calls **`editIdea`** with **`isPublished`** flipped. **`isPublished`** is camelCase (matches Swift **`EditIdeaRequestBody`**). Adjust **`title`/`purpose`** to match the idea or fetch first via **List ideas**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete idea (deleteIdea)",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/ideas/{{ideaId}}",
            "description": "Maps to **`IdeaController.deleteIdea`** ā€” **`204`** success."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Objectives",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Add objective (addObjective)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data && data.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('objectiveId', data.id);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"text\": \"Ship MVP\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/objectives",
            "description": "Maps to **`ObjectiveController.addObjective`** / **`POST /objectives`**. Response **`201`** with **`id`**, **`text`**, **`is_completed`** ā€” Tests script saves **`objectiveId`**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Modify objective (modifyObjective)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"text\": \"Updated objective text\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/objectives/{{objectiveId}}",
            "description": "Maps to **`ObjectiveController.modifyObjective`** ā€” **`PATCH /objectives/:id`**, **`200`**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Complete objective (completeObjective)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/objectives/{{objectiveId}}/complete",
            "description": "Maps to **`ObjectiveController.completeObjective`** ā€” **`POST /objectives/:id/complete`** (no body); toggles **`is_completed`**, **`200`**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete objective (deleteObjective)",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/objectives/{{objectiveId}}",
            "description": "Maps to **`ObjectiveController.deleteObjective`** ā€” **`204`**."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
